.TH "async_xor_val" 9 "async_xor_val" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
async_xor_val \- attempt a xor parity check with a dma engine.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct dma_async_tx_descriptor *" async_xor_val
.BI "(struct page *dest "  ","
.BI "struct page **src_list "  ","
.BI "unsigned int offset "  ","
.BI "int src_cnt "  ","
.BI "size_t len "  ","
.BI "enum sum_check_flags *result "  ","
.BI "struct async_submit_ctl *submit "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dest" 12
destination page used if the xor is performed synchronously
.IP "src_list" 12
array of source pages
.IP "offset" 12
offset in pages to start transaction
.IP "src_cnt" 12
number of source pages
.IP "len" 12
length in bytes
.IP "result" 12
0 if sum == 0 else non-zero
.IP "submit" 12
submission / completion modifiers
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
honored flags: ASYNC_TX_ACK

src_list note: if the dest is also a source it must be at index zero.
The contents of this array will be overwritten if a scribble region
is not specified.
